name: RenderTypeGroup
description: A set of functionally equivalent shaders. One using DefaultVertexFormat.BLOCK , and the other two using DefaultVertexFormat.NEW_ENTITY . entityFabulous may support custom render targets and other aspects of the fabulous pipeline, or can otherwise be the same as entity .

fields.name: block
fields.description: The field for the block record component.

fields.name: entity
fields.description: The field for the entity record component.

fields.name: entityFabulous
fields.description: The field for the entityFabulous record component.

constructors.name: RenderTypeGroup
constructors.description: Creates an instance of a RenderTypeGroup record class.

methods.name: isEmpty
methods.description: Returns true if this group has render types or not. It either has all, or none.

methods.name: toString
methods.description: Returns a string representation of this record class. The representation contains the name of the class, followed by the name and value of each of the record components.

methods.name: hashCode
methods.description: Returns a hash code value for this object. The value is derived from the hash code of each of the record components.

methods.name: equals
methods.description: Indicates whether some other object is "equal to" this one. The objects are equal if the other object is of the same class and if all the record components are equal. All components in this record class are compared with Objects::equals(Object,Object) .

methods.name: block
methods.description: Returns the value of the block record component.

methods.name: entity
methods.description: Returns the value of the entity record component.

methods.name: entityFabulous
methods.description: Returns the value of the entityFabulous record component.
